According to the World Coal Association (WCA), the global network for the coal industry, coal remains a key commodity across the planet, despite the demand for cleaner energy sources. Investors, government, coal producers and other industry organisations should therefore contribute to accelerating the use of cleaner and more efficient coal technologies, WCA chief executive, Benjamin Sporton tells Sascha Solomons. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 8 2018. It will be published online on the 31st August 2018. You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy